Glaxo, Vodafone Make Plans for Euro Zone Split, Observer Says

-- B y   K e v i n   C r o w l e y
-- 
2011-12-04T15:55:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-04/glaxo-vodafone-make-plans-for-euro-zone-split-observer-says.html
GlaxoSmithKline Plc (GSK)  and  Vodafone
Group Plc (VOD)  are among U.K. companies making contingency plans for
a potential break-up of the group of countries using the euro,
the  Observer  said, citing company spokesmen.  GlaxoSmithKline is preparing to ensure the uninterrupted
flow of funds between countries to continue its operations, the
newspaper said, citing a spokesman. Vodafone is ready to
implement contingency plans if the situation in Europe changes,
the Observer reported, also citing a company spokesman.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kevin Crowley in London at 
